  "texts": [
    "To reduce memory usage and potentially promote generalization via shared representations, we ultimately use the same underlying LLM to role-play as both the critic and the policy.",
    "Our ablations (see Appendix D.2) empirically support that using a shared LLM for the critic and the policy improves performance.",
    "Data Mixing.",
    "In addition, by sharing the same underlying LLM, we can substantially simplify the concrete algorithm by mixing both the critic and policy rollouts in the same batch to compute advantage and loss.",
    "This allows us to remove the need for alternating updates between the critic and the policy and instead perform all updates in a single batch."
  ],
